### 3.2.3 Regional landscape: data center overview across key Indian cities

![](data:image/png;base64,)

Primary and Secondary Markets in India

Source: C&W Research

The Indian data center market is distributed among these 7 markets: Mumbai, Delhi NCR, Chennai, Hyderabad, Bengaluru, Pune and Kolkata. These cities are India's fastest growing data center clusters.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

City-wise market share (IT MW) (As of March 31, 2025)

Source: C&W Research, SISL

Mumbai's dominance can be attributed to its strategic importance as India's economic and financial capital. The city's subsea cable landing stations further strengthens its appeal as a data center destination, ensuring low-latency global connectivity. Chennai, with subsea connectivity advantages, has also emerged as a preferred location for operators targeting southern India and international markets.
